Author: Alright#0419
Content:
general update on LABS... 

Cannot contact joker at all. This isn't normal. Even when he fucks off for a few days on discord, I have other means of communication that he would normally respond with. 

If I don't hear from him within about a day, we will start transitioning all of our infra to komodoplatform repos prior to the fork. There's a good chance ac_notarypay will need to be disabled for a little while. I'm deathly afraid to touch it other than deactivating it entirely. I'm not confident I won't introduce an inflation bug.

The CFEK cluster is likely to die off for a little while as well.

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: the KMDLabs repo is solid... the revertHF branch has been working for me so if it was all pushed to master... then KMDLabs/komodo/tree/master should be fine

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: then only issue I see so far is the one kmdkrazy found early on before this all borked to hell...

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: and that is a corrupted wallet.dat will kill what should be a working node and stop it from syncing properly.

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: for NN... wiping komodo and .komodo directories, then rebuilding KMDLabs/komodo/tree/revertHF  as your daemon and cli will get ypu in sync... sync in manually not with NN start script

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: you will need to bootstrap KMD... no getting around that as for some reason... this version gets stuck at this height I noted yesterday...

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content:
``` "blocks": 1635295,
  "longestchain": 1660848,
after that it would never start the daemon sadly...
Error: Failed to connect best block```

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: So instead... bootstrap it and then manually run it to get to best height.

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: Then edit assetchains.json in StakedNotary directory to remove all but LABS. With any luck, start.sh should now run properly.

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: As far as StakedNotary goes... the pos64 branch might not fully work for everyone... and I am not sure which branch should be reverted to...

Content: It does appear @Alright pushed commits to the master branch, so we may be good to use master for both going forward... will require someone other than me to test.... im going to be out for several more hours tonight
